metadata.name: Over the Air #331
metadata.description:
During the last couple of decades, over the air television signals and antennas switched to digital, bringing with them a new form of static and distortion as the signal is broken up. "Over the Air" is inspired by these digital distortions, incorporating aspects of them into the same grid-like structure seen on the television. Additional patterns are combined in the grid with these distortions to create the final artwork.

Patterns for the individual blocks in the grid are divided into categories, and various amounts are picked for each work, with dozens of possible mixtures. Patterns can flow in different directions across the varied canvases. Distribution of these patterns across the grid varies from work to work, providing for different feels as they bunch together or spread apart.

metadata.name: VOYAGERS #111
metadata.description:
Generative animated painting made from looping gestures in a virtual void.

Voyagers is an exploration of automated gestures and screenspace layering effects. Each brush stroke sweeps through the canvas leaving a trail of color that either disappears or mixes with adjacent colors. The image slowly builds up to achieve an equilibrium between the rhythm of the gestures and the interaction of color values. These colors are quantized and dithered to produce chunky, textured, blocks of light that reify the materiality of the screen and the pixel. Two aspect ratios are possible, each with its own material relationship to screen-based work, 1:1 and 4:3 (vertical).

Press 's' to save looping animated GIF (live mode only).
Press 'p' to pause the animation.
Press 'c' to capture a single frame.
Made with P5.js and GLSL. By @galoandstuff.

metadata.name: The Climb #27
metadata.description:
The climb is about the search for purpose.

Everyone needs a purpose, a path that leads somewhere. Whether you reach it or not is not the point, it’s about the climb. The search for a purpose gives our life meaning. It gives us a reason to look for something more.

Unfortunately, there is no universal truth as to what your purpose in life is. Everyone is unique. Different. We are the product of our upbringing, environment and the cumulative sum of thousands of microdecisions. We need to find meaning for ourselves. Our unique meaning. On this path, we climb alone.

“The Climb” is created to be raw, unique, beautiful and violently volatile, much like our lives.


Everything is written in javascript and p5js.
It can sometimes take a little while to render on older computers.

metadata.name: Morixels Mans #1076
metadata.description:
The Morixels Mans is unique Random Generated 10,000 PFP NFTs, and this collection is for people like me who are nostalgic for pixel arts.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 24 by 24 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution. 
The number of Traits in this collection is 12 (120 layers) and it has the ability to make 31,091,558,400 NFTs.
Some ​layers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.
To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

Designed by: @morteza_yousefy
Made in 2022

metadata.name: Treasured Rug #192
metadata.description:
A form of concrete poetry depicting a rug.
Typography created by multiple lines of typewriter text.
Features one of five possible character sets.
One of ten possible palettes for text color
90% chance of black paper, or 10% chance of white
10% chance of rare "Wild" character shift, otherwise 45% of either "Loose" or "Tight"
15% chance each of either rare "Narrow" or "Wide" rug otherwise "Standard"
3 styles of paper grain
Differing line gaps
Differing types of skew effect
Differing types of blend effect when characters overlay.

Press S to save in High Resolution

Uses p5.js and scribble.js
@p1x3lboy August 2022

metadata.name: Deep Space Grid - AI Study III #84
metadata.description:
Deep Space Grid uses experimentation with lines, shapes, color and opacity through the exploration of faux space charts.

Adjusts to monitor size, best viewed in fullscreen mode.

This project is a generative art experiment using a Text2Code workflow. The JavaScript code for this project was written entirely by AI using GPT-3. None of the code was altered or created by a human aside from changing Math.random() with fxrand().

Text2Code study #3 /// Project CoDexter by @BrainArtLabs

A simple particle system, folded, convolved, distorted and decorated into something wild and beautiful.
